cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about incorporating latent sentence structure into neural machine translation models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, so categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of RNN and CNN encoders, which are commonly used in neural networks for natural language processing and computer vision, respectively, so categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are also possible.
